ding which historical statement is correct or intended.\n30\t- Summarizing, ranking, embedding, or otherwise interpreting conversations.\n31\t- Controlling an agent, enforcing a workflow, or orchestrating agents.\n32\t- Capturing hidden model reasoning or claiming it can reproduce a native agent\n33\t  session.\n34\t\n35\tThose belong to clients such as Turnbridge and Intent Recall, not to this core\n36\tstorage layer.\n37\t","tool_use_id":"toolu_01QaYdSDcNB5KjQ2C7Sxif3p","type":"tool_result"}],"role":"user"},"parentUuid":"e1bb12db-486a-4b0e-bc43-16f362aeb287","promptId":"c4c659c5-32f9-448e-8ca7-bbe19d257601","sessionId":"700cd82f-2f79-4cd6-b727-0f81230e0837","session_id":"700cd82f-2f79-4cd6-b727-0f81230e0837","slug":"quirky-shimmying-spark","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"e1bb12db-486a-4b0e-bc43-16f362aeb287","timestamp":"2026-07-18T22:12:13.910Z","toolUseResult":{"file":{"content":"# Product intent\n\n## Purpose\n\nConversation Ledger preserves durable, inspectable records of visible\nconversations between people and coding agents. It is a general conversation\nprovenance primitive, not an intent-analysis product. Downstream consumers may\nuse its records as evidence about why a repository changed, but the ledger must\nnot impose that interpretation.\n\nThe record must remain useful to consumers beyond a single tool: cross-CLI\ncontinuity, archival/export, code attribution, review, and later intent\nretrieval are all valid independent uses.\n\n## Behavioral commitments\n\n- Preserve source material and provenance; do not silently rewrite history.\n- Preserve exact visible turns before creating optional derived views.\n- Retain enough provenance for consumers to determine applicability without\n  treating any record as timeless truth.\n- Record the repository, branch, commit, worktree state, author, timestamps,\n  and capture mechanism with each artifact whenever available.\n- Keep storage out of ordinary working-tree status views while retaining normal\n  Git durability and shareability.\n- Make sharing, retention, redaction, and deletion deliberate user choices.\n\n## Non-goals for the foundation\n\n- Deciding which historical statement is correct or intended.\n- Summarizing, ranking, embedding, or otherwise interpreting conversations.\n- Controlling an agent, enforcing a workflow, or orchestrating agents.\n- Capturing hidden model reasoning or claiming it can reproduce a native agent\n  session.\n\nThose belong to clients such as Turnbridge and Intent Recall, not to this core\nstorage layer.\n","filePath":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger/docs/PRODUCT_INTENT.md","numLines":37,"startLine":1,"totalLines":37},"type":"text"},"type":"user","userType":"external","uuid":"08e97e68-2846-4b81-8979-39a95ef1087d","version":"2.1.214"},"format":"claude-code-jsonl/1"},"recorded_at":"2026-07-18T22:48:08.070Z","schema":"conversation-ledger/v1"}
{"actor":{"type":"human"},"content":{"blocks":[{"content":"1\t# WIP technical design\n2\t\n3\t**Status:** exploratory; no compatibility promises.\n4\t\n5\t## Scope\n6\t\n7\tConversation Ledger will define a canonical append-only event format plus a local,\n8\tGit-backed storage protocol. It must preserve exact visible content while\n9\tsupporting efficient indexes and later derived views.\n10\t\n11\t## Canonical objects\n12\t\n13\tAn `EvidenceEvent` is immutable and has:\n14\t\n15\t- `id`, `schema_version`, and content hash;\n16\t- `kind` (`conversation_turn`, `decision`, `document`, `annotation`,\n17\t  `redaction`, or `supersession`);\n18\t- `occurred_at` and `recorded_at` timestamps;\n19\t- `actor` and `producer` provenance;\n20\t- a content reference and media type;\n21\t- repository context: repository identity, branch, `HEAD` SHA, worktree ID,\n22\t  and optional dirty-worktree fingerprint;\n23\t- optional links to related events.\n24\t\n25\tConversation turns preserve visible roles, textual content, tool calls, and\n26\ttool results as supplied by their capture adapter. The source-native payload\n27\tmay be retained as an opaque, versioned attachment for lossless export. Hidden\n28\treasoning is neither requested nor represented.\n29\t\n30\tAn append-only `Conversation` manifest provides ordering and identifies the\n31\tsource CLI's session ID. Derived data must remain separately identifiable from\n32\traw captured events.\n33\t\n34\t## Storage proposal\n35\t\n36\tThe primary candidate is Git objects plus a dedicated notes ref such as\n37\t`refs/notes/conversation-ledger`:\n38\t\n39\t1. Canonical event payloads are content-addressed blobs.\n40\t2. A compact manifest/index points to those blobs.\n41\t3. Git notes associated with a source commit point to the applicable manifest.\n42\t4. Events created against uncommitted work use the current `HEAD` plus a\n43\t   worktree/diff fingerprint in their context.\n44\t\n45\tThis keeps the working tree and `git status` clean, unlike tracked transcript\n46\tfiles. It also avoids a separately checked-out data branch. Fetch/push support\n47\tfor the notes ref will be explicit and opt-in.\n48\t\n49\tThe exact ref layout, garbage-collection rules, and multi-worktree behavior\n50\tare open questions.\n51\t\n52\t## API direction\n53\t\n54\tThe first library/CLI boundary should expose:\n55\t\n56\t- append an immutable event or conversation turn;\n57\t- read a conversation in stable order;\n58\t- enumerate records by repository context, author, source, and ancestry;\n59\t- attach annotations, redactions, and supersession relationships;\n60\t- import/export a complete canonical conversation without data loss;\n61\t- an adapter cursor/checkpoint API for incremental capture.\n62\t\n63\tQuery ranking, semantic search, agent-facing synthesis, and vendor-native\n64\tsession fabrication are explicitly out of scope here.\n65\t\n66\t## Privacy and integrity\n67\t\n68\tVisible tool output can contain secrets. Capture must support exclusion rules,\n69\tredaction events, local-only storage, and clearly distinguish captured content\n70\tfrom derived metadata. Content hashes should make accidental mutation\n71\tdetectable; redaction removes access through a new manifest rather than\n72\tpretending the original event never existed. The retention and remote-sharing\n73\tpolicy must be configured by the repository owner.\n74\t","tool_use_id":"toolu_01RCwnNNWa4J82iGNy2P4EWD","type":"tool_result"}],"role":"user"},"context":{"cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","dirty_fingerprint":"e12e6fe04f3a78e3a5f3ff041be237d2a899e1d55f1148de6f18442622160697","repo":"conversation-ledger"},"conversation":{"id":"claude-code:700cd82f-2f79-4cd6-b727-0f81230e0837","seq":31},"id":"ev1-227ad7553c06b3284274ee41718644b8f0f1a999fb3dfa505130c1178853eb05","kind":"conversation_turn","occurred_at":"2026-07-18T22:12:23.336Z","producer":{"session_id":"700cd82f-2f79-4cd6-b727-0f81230e0837","source":"claude-cod