\n\nconversation-ledger (this repo) is the foundation of a 3-repo ecosystem, all design-stage as of 2026-07-18:\n- `../turnbridge` — captures/transfers visible conversations between coding CLIs (adapters, cursors); first producer.\n- `../intent-recall` — later evidence retrieval about repo intent; first consumer. Wants generic evidence kinds (decisions, documents), not just conversation turns, and sub-turn citation anchors eventually.\n- `/Users/evintunador/repos/BandaruDheeraj/sticky-note` (singular) — Dheeraj's shipped Node CLI (npm `sticky-note-cli`, v3) for AI-session team handoff; referenced as a structural template: git-native storage (orphan `sticky-note/data` branch + `refs/notes/sticky-note`), hook-driven capture, MCP server, field-level merge driver.\n\nThe user's hard constraint: the ledger must stay a small standalone general utility (unix tool-composition philosophy) — storage/provenance only, no interpretation, no orchestration. Closest prior art found (2026-07): git-memento (transcripts in git notes, commit-linked); differentiators are the normalized multi-CLI schema, append-only evidence events, manifest-based redaction, content-addressed blobs under one dedicated ref, explicit opt-in sync. See [[feedback-liberal-small-subagents]].\n","filePath":"/Users/evintunador/.claude/projects/-Users-evintunador-repos-evintunador-conversation-ledger/memory/project-ledger-ecosystem.md","memdirStamped":true,"originalFile":null,"structuredPatch":[],"type":"create","userModified":false},"type":"user","userType":"external","uuid":"3a4431b8-336f-4b77-88a9-e4ccdb583404","version":"2.1.214"},"format":"claude-code-jsonl/1"},"recorded_at":"2026-07-18T22:48:08.070Z","schema":"conversation-ledger/v1"}
