nch (sticky-note v3 style)"}],"question":"How should events physically live in git? (Your WIP doc proposes notes as primary; I have a concern about that.)"},{"header":"Today's MVP","multiSelect":false,"options":[{"description":"init/append/log/show/list/export + cursor checkpoints, plus a reference importer that ingests this very Claude Code session from ~/.claude/projects JSONL — proving the design end-to-end on real data. Importer lives in contrib/ to keep the core neutral (adapters are turnbridge's job).","label":"Core CLI + one real importer (Recommended)"},{"description":"The storage boundary alone: append/read/list/export/import over JSONL stdin/stdout. Purest scope; you'd test it with hand-made events until turnbridge exists.","label":"Core CLI only"},{"description":"Design the importable API as the primary artifact (what turnbridge/intent-recall will call), CLI as a thin wrapper. Slower to a demo, strongest foundation for the siblings.","label":"Library-first, thin CLI"}],"question":"What should exist by end of today for this to count as 'a reality'?"},{"header":"CLI name","multiSelect":false,"options":[{"description":"Short, greppable, unclaimed. `cledger append`, `cledger log`. Also naming the binary git-cledger would make `git cledger` work automatically.","label":"cledger (Recommended)"},{"description":"Friendlier: `convo append`, `convo log`. Slightly higher collision risk and less obviously ledger-ish.","label":"convo"},{"description":"Reads as native git: `git ledger append`. Leans fully into git-backed identity, but 'ledger' alone is generic and collides with accounting tools (ledger-cli).","label":"git-ledger (git subcommand)"},{"description":"Maximum clarity, zero collisions; users alias it themselves. Verbose for a daily-driver CLI.","label":"conversation-ledger, no abbreviation"}],"question":"What should the installed command be called?"}]},"type":"user","userType":"external","uuid":"d6ac17a8-7b02-4d31-900c-469e6f1c81a7","version":"2.1.214"},"for