{"actor":{"type":"human"},"content":{"blocks":[{"content":[{"text":"# Competitive Landscape: AI Coding-Agent Conversation Capture/Storage\n\n## Capture-only tools (no durable git-native storage)\n\n**SpecStory** (specstory.com) — Commercial CLI/extension capturing Cursor, Claude Code, Copilot, Codex, Gemini CLI chats. Reads `~/.claude/projects/*.jsonl` etc., converts to markdown, writes to `.specstory/history/` **inside the working tree** (tracked files, dirties git status unless gitignored). No commit linking natively; has cloud sync and a \"Lore\" feature to mine sessions into reusable skills. Differs: writes plain tracked files, not content-addressed git objects; optional cloud upload; product is search/reuse, not provenance.\n\n**aider** `.aider.chat.history.md` — Built-in flat markdown transcript file in the repo root, appended per session. No structure, no commit linkage, no redaction, not git-native at all (just a regular file you'd `.gitignore` or commit manually).\n\n**Claude Code `~/.claude/projects/*.jsonl`** and **Codex CLI `~/.codex/sessions/YYYY/MM/DD/rollout-*.jsonl(.zst)`** — Internal per-machine JSONL transcript stores used for `/resume`/`codex resume`. Undocumented, version-fragile schema, purely local (not in any repo, not shareable, no provenance/redaction model).\n\n**Continue.dev** — `.continue/dev_data` local telemetry of dev interactions; anonymized-optional PostHog telemetry upstream. Not git-notes based, not commit-linked.\n\n## Session browsers/search (read existing stores, don't restructure them)\n\n**cass / coding_agent_session_search** (Dicklesworthstone) and **agent-sessions** (jazzyalex) — Index/search/resume across 11+ providers' native session files. cass has some \"provenance correlation\" (project-scoped, explicit-reference anchored) but treats provenance as a search-quality signal, not a durable attributable record; storage stays in each tool's native per-machine location (SQLite index layered on top).\n\n## Commit-trailer provenance (metadata, not transcripts)\n\n**ai-trailers, \"Assisted-by\" convention, Lore protocol** (arXiv:2603.15566, lore-protocol.com) — Encode AI involvement as git trailers in commit messages (`Assisted-by:`, decision records). Queryable via `git log --trailer=`. Captures *reasoning summaries*, not full conversations; no separate object store, no redaction mechanism, commit-message bloat is the tradeoff.\n\n## Git-notes-based AI provenance (closest architectural relatives)\n\n**git-memento** (mandel-macaque/memento) — Git extension storing AI session data as git notes: `refs/notes/commits` for summaries, `refs/notes/memento-full-audit` for full transcripts. Explicit `git memento commit <session-id>` links Provider/Session-ID to the exact commit; opt-in by design (you choose what to attach); supports Codex and Claude Code. **This is the nearest prior art** — same core mechanism (notes, not working-tree files; per-commit linkage; opt-in). Differs from conversation-ledger: two providers only vs. normalized multi-agent schema; per-commit attach flow rather than append-only evidence-event log; no content-addressing or redaction-via-manifest; single combined ref rather than a dedicated content-addressed blob store.\n\n**Agent Note** (wasabeef) — `refs/notes/agentnote`, git-hook-linked at commit time. Stores prompt/response *summaries* + AI-ratio estimate, not full transcripts. No explicit redaction or opt-in push/fetch controls (notes sync like normal notes, \"if you push, teammates read it\").\n\n**Git AI** (usegitai.com, git-ai-project/git-ai) — `refs/notes/ai` stores attribution *metadata only* (file/line-range → session mapping); full transcripts live externally (local/cloud/self-hosted), referenced via `messages_url`. Notes auto-sync on push/fetch (no explicit opt-in gate). Deliberately keeps content out of git for size/privacy — the opposite tradeoff from conversation-ledger's \"store the evidence\" stance.\n\n## Server/DB-based platforms\n\n**AgentLogs** — Self-hostable observability platform (SQLite + blob storage, Docker), links sessions to commits, team dashboards, secret redaction. Not git-native at all — separate service/DB, not a repo-local artifact.\n\n**AI Commit Ledger** (research paper) — Deterministic commit↔session attribution matching (94.2% accuracy) writing structured \"AI Receipts\" to a dedicated metadata *branch*. Notably stores only a SHA-256 hash of the transcript, never raw content — privacy-by-omission rather than redaction-by-manifest.\n\n**ProjectMem** (arXiv:2606.12329) and **DiffMem** — Local-first, git-native, append-only *event logs* for agent memory (issue/attempt/fix/decision), grep/diff-able flat markdown/text files in the repo, default-on redaction. Close in spirit (append-only, git-native, redaction-aware) but files live in the working tree as trackable content, not as content-addressed blobs under a dedicated ref — and they're memory/summarization products, not raw-transcript provenance stores.\n\n## Prior art for the git-notes/hidden-ref architecture itself\n\n**git-bug**, **git-appraise**, Gerrit's NoteDb — Distributed issue trackers / code review systems storing structured JSON records in `refs/notes/devtools/*`-style namespaces, using git's `cat_sort_uniq` merge driver for conflict-free append. Strong non-AI architectural precedent for \"clean working tree, dedicated ref, JSON blobs, explicit sync\" — validates the approach but none touch AI conversations.\n\n---\n\n**(a) Three closest competitors:** git-memento (nearly identical mechanism: dual notes refs, full transcript + summary, per-commit session linkage, opt-in), Agent Note (git-notes, hook-based commit linkage, but summaries only), Git AI (git-notes attribution but transcripts kept out of git — inverse tradeoff).\n\n**(b) Gaps nobody covers:** (1) a *normalized* schema spanning Claude Code, Codex CLI, Cursor, and aider uniformly — every existing tool is single/dual-provider; (2) append-only evidence-event storage with **redaction via new manifests** (rewrite-free, auditable redaction) — none of the git-notes tools have this, they either store raw text forever or omit content entirely; (3) true content-addressed blobs under one dedicated ref with explicit, separately-gated opt-in push/fetch (most either auto-sync notes on push or don't sync at all); (4) a minimal, dependency-free unix-style CLI rather than a commercial/cloud platform (SpecStory, AgentLogs, Git AI all have cloud tiers).\n\n**(c) Evidence this exact idea exists:** No exact match. git-memento is the closest single precedent for \"transcripts as git notes, commit-linked, opt-in,\" but lacks content-addressing, multi-agent normalization, and manifest-based redaction — conversation-ledger's specific combination appears to be a genuine, if narrow, gap.\n\nSources: [SpecStory](https://specstory.com/), [SpecStory docs](https://docs.specstory.com/integrations/terminal-coding-agents), [aider chat history](https://aider.chat/docs/config/options.html), [aider FAQ](https://aider.chat/docs/faq.html), [Claude Code sessions](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/sessions), [Claude Code JSONL format](https://claude-dev.tools/docs/jsonl-format), [Codex resume guide](https://www.verdent.ai/guides/codex-cli-resume-continue-save-chat), [git-bug](https://github.com/git-bug/git-bug), [git-appraise (DeepWiki)](https://deepwiki.com/google/git-appraise), [Assisted-by trailer](https://www.baristalabs.io/blog/ai-assisted-commits-need-provenance-trailer), [ai-trailers](https://github.com/EslaMx7/ai-trailers), [Lore protocol paper](https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.15566), [git-memento](https://github.com/mandel-macaque/memento), [Git AI docs](https://usegitai.com/docs/cli/how-git-ai-works), [Agent Note](https://dev.to/wasabeef/introducing-agent-note-saving-the-why-behind-ai-assisted-code-in-git-30a8), [AgentLogs](https://github.com/agentlogs/agentlogs), [AI Commit Ledger](https://www.researchgate.net/publication/402524035_AI_Commit_Ledger_Bridging_the_AI_Transparency_Gap_in_Version_Control_with_Deterministic_Session_Attribution), [ProjectMem](https://arxiv.org/html/2606.12329), [DiffMem](https://github.com/Growth-Kinetics/DiffMem), [cass](https://github.com/Dicklesworthstone/coding_agent_session_search), [agent-sessions](https://github.com/jazzyalex/agent-sessions), [Continue.dev dev data](https://docs.continue.dev/development-data)","type":"text"},{"text":"agentId: af424cc63295b8016 (use SendMessage with to: 'af424cc63295b8016', summary: '<5-10 word recap>' to continue this agent)\n<usage>subagent_tokens: 48520\ntool_uses: 18\nduration_ms: 116421</usage>","type":"text"}],"tool_use_id":"toolu_01CR25vN4kXAqVjhFiWtWFSm","type":"tool_result"}],"role":"user"},"context":{"cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","dirty_fingerprint":"e12e6fe04f3a78e3a5f3ff041be237d2a899e1d55f1148de6f18442622160697","repo":"conversation-ledger"},"conversation":{"id":"claude-code:700cd82f-2f79-4cd6-b727-0f81230e0837","seq":43},"id":"ev1-8ffa7b8e23d3bba393739d7017426c7c0d91db58163082f81b92dca283fc37f1","kind":"conversation_turn","occurred_at":"2026-07-18T22:14:59.883Z","producer":{"session_id":"700cd82f-2f79-4cd6-b727-0f81230e0837","source":"claude-code","tool":"cledger","version":"0.1.0"},"raw":{"data":{"cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","entrypoint":"cli","gitBranch":"main","isSidechain":false,"message":{"content":[{"content":[{"text":"# Competitive Landscape: AI Coding-Agent Conversation Capture/Storage\n\n## Capture-only tools (no durable git-native storage)\n\n**SpecStory** (specstory.com) — Commercial CLI/extension capturing Cursor, Claude Code, Copilot, Codex, Gemini CLI chats. Reads `~/.claude/projects/*.jsonl` etc., converts to markdown, writes to `.specstory/history/` **inside the working tree** (tracked files, dirties git status unless gitignored). No commit linking natively; has cloud sync and a \"Lore\" feature to mine sessions into reusable skills. Differs: writes plain tracked files, not