rxiv.org/abs/2603.15566), [git-memento](https://github.com/mandel-macaque/memento), [Git AI docs](https://usegitai.com/docs/cli/how-git-ai-works), [Agent Note](https://dev.to/wasabeef/introducing-agent-note-saving-the-why-behind-ai-assisted-code-in-git-30a8), [AgentLogs](https://github.com/agentlogs/agentlogs), [AI Commit Ledger](https://www.researchgate.net/publication/402524035_AI_Commit_Ledger_Bridging_the_AI_Transparency_Gap_in_Version_Control_with_Deterministic_Session_Attribution), [ProjectMem](https://arxiv.org/html/2606.12329), [DiffMem](https://github.com/Growth-Kinetics/DiffMem), [cass](https://github.com/Dicklesworthstone/coding_agent_session_search), [agent-sessions](https://github.com/jazzyalex/agent-sessions), [Continue.dev dev data](https://docs.continue.dev/development-data)","type":"text"}],"prompt":"Do web research on existing tools/projects that capture, store, share, or replay AI coding-assistant conversation history, and report a competitive landscape summary.\n\nContext: I'm building \"conversation-ledger\": a small standalone unix-style utility that stores normalized, provenance-preserving records of visible coding-agent conversations (Claude Code, Codex CLI, Cursor, aider, etc.) in a git repository — likely as content-addressed blobs referenced from a dedicated git ref like refs/notes/conversation-ledger, so the working tree and git status stay clean. Append-only evidence events with repo/branch/commit/author provenance, redaction via new manifests, explicit opt-in push/fetch. NOT an intent-analysis, summarization, or memory product — just durable attributable storage.\n\nSearch for (at minimum):\n- SpecStory (specstory.com) — captures Cursor/Claude Code chat history\n- aider's --chat-history / .aider.chat.history.md approach\n- Claude Code's own ~/.claude/projects transcript JSONL storage and /resume; claude-code session sharing tools on GitHub\n- Tools storing data in git-notes or hidden git refs (e.g. git-bug, git-appraise, gerrit's NoteDb