{"actor":{"type":"human"},"content":{"blocks":[{"content":[{"text":"## Analysis Report: Turnbridge and Intent Recall\n\n### 1. Purpose, Scope, and Non-Goals\n\n**Turnbridge** (capture layer)\n- **Purpose**: Lossless visible-conversation continuity between coding agent CLIs. Captures native local transcript formats, normalizes turns, and enables resume across different tools/providers.\n- **Scope**: CLI-specific adapters that tail transcript artifacts incrementally, parse completed turns, normalize content/tool-calls, and write to Conversation Ledger. Unified picker and rehydration UI across supported CLIs. Incremental cursor tracking.\n- **Non-goals**: Team presence, task tracking, orchestration. Inferring or replacing human intent. Depending on undocumented native session-file writes as core mechanism.\n\n**Intent Recall** (retrieval layer)\n- **Purpose**: Evidence-backed retrieval of historical repository intent. Answer \"what behavior was actually intended?\" by exposing underlying evidence and distinguishing original requests from later changes of mind.\n- **Scope**: Consume immutable events from Conversation Ledger, build derived versioned indexes, support structured evidence classes (human requests, decisions, specifications, tests/code), return evidence with citations, chronology, and provenance.\n- **Non-goals**: Establishing single permanent truth. Replacing product judgment or user confirmation. Capturing sessions or transferring conversations.\n\n---\n\n### 2. Concrete Expectations on Conversation Ledger\n\n**Turnbridge requirements** (WIP_TECHNICAL_DESIGN + PRODUCT_INTENT):\n\n- **Append-only event storage**: \"After each completed visible turn, it normalizes newly observed material and appends it to Conversation Ledger.\"\n- **Incremental cursor semantics**: Adapters must track cursor position to capture turns incrementally without modifying source transcripts. Tolerates incomplete final lines and schema changes.\n- **Normalized turn schema** must include:\n  - Role/content (user, assistant messages)\n  - Tool calls and results\n  - Source CLI identifier and originating transcript metadata\n  - Repository/session identity (repo, branch, HEAD hash) for filtering compatible conversations\n- **Canonical event ordering** for rehydration: \"The target adapter receives canonical events in order\"\n- **Partial capture handling**: \"The MVP must retain raw incremental capture, present partial capture honestly\"\n\n**Intent Recall requirements** (WIP_TECHNICAL_DESIGN + PRODUCT_INTENT):\n\n- **Immutable, addressable events**: \"Intent Recall consumes immutable events from Conversation Ledger and builds derived, versioned indexes. Raw evidence always remains addressable.\"\n- **Event ID granularity**: \"Derived claims must reference the exact event IDs and excerpts from which they were made\" (open question: turn, paragraph, sentence, or span level?)\n- **Rich metadata for filtering**: Must support queries by repository/code-state context, chronology, and eventually semantic indexing.\n- **Support multiple evidence classes**: Treat human requests, decisions, specs, tests, and code as distinct types within the same ledger (not just conversation turns).\n- **Provenance and citations**: Each stored item needs lineage data (who, when, source).\n\n---\n\n### 3. Contradictions and Tensions\n\n**Scope creep vs. generality**:\n- Turnbridge focuses narrowly on \"user-visible turn history—messages, tool calls, tool results\" and explicitly avoids claiming to preserve \"hidden reasoning\" or \"provider-private session state.\"\n- Intent Recall broadens the definition: \"Specifications and documentation\" and \"tests and code, linked as implementation artifacts.\" It also states: \"Turnbridge is one valuable producer of conversational evidence, but Lens must also support decisions and artifacts that arrived through other ingestion paths.\"\n- This implies Conversation Ledger must be a *general-purpose evidence store*, not just a conversation transcript ledger. Turnbridge is only one producer.\n\n**Granularity mismatch**:\n- Turnbridge operates at turn granularity (completed turns are the atomic unit).\n- Intent Recall explicitly questions its own needs: \"What source-link granularity is useful: turn, paragraph, sentence, or span?\" This is unresolved and may require Conversation Ledger to support sub-turn citations.\n\n**Indexing and retrieval scope**:\n- Turnbridge assumes it owns discovery (tailoring local transcripts) and append logic.\n- Intent Recall needs \"lexical, structural, and eventually semantic indexes\" over the ledger—suggesting Conversation Ledger must expose queryability, not just append-only semantics.\n\n---\n\n### 4. MVP Dependency Order\n\n**Clear priority: conversation-ledger first, then Turnbridge, then Intent Recall.**\n\n- Intent Recall explicitly reads from conversation-ledger: \"Intent Recall reads Conversation Ledger directly\" (PRODUCT_INTENT).\n- Turnbridge is a client: \"Conversation Ledger owns the durable neutral record\" (PRODUCT_INTENT).\n- Turnbridge must ship first to populate the ledger that Intent Recall consumes.\n\n**Minimal conversation-ledger MVP should provide**:\n1. Append-only event storage with immutable, addressable IDs\n2. Incremental cursor tracking (for Turnbridge adapters)\n3. Normalized turn schema: role, content, tool calls, source CLI, repository metadata\n4. Ordered retrieval (for rehydration and chronological evidence)\n5. Per-event or per-excerpt citation anchors (for Intent Recall's evidence linking)\n\n**Deferred to post-MVP**:\n- Semantic indexing (Intent Recall's \"eventually semantic indexes\")\n- Sub-turn granularity (until Intent Recall resolves its open question)\n- Multi-producer ingestion paths beyond Turnbridge (until Intent Recall is ready)\n- Advanced query filtering (Intent Recall can build this as a derived layer)","type":"text"}],"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q9tGE1VZNnYTgjojYKusCo","type":"tool_result"}],"role":"user"},"context":{