ing, cwd: string): Promise<void>` — same shape as the Claude one; summary line `cledger: codex +N events (M deduped)`.\n\nRollout format (~/.codex/sessions/YYYY/MM/DD/rollout-<ts>-<uuid>.jsonl), one JSON object per line with {type, payload} (lines MAY also carry a top-level `timestamp` — use it when present). Line types: session_meta (first line; payload.session_id, payload.cwd, payload.cli_version), turn_context, event_msg, response_item, world_state.\n\nConvert ONLY response_item lines with payload.type in: \"message\", \"function_call\", \"function_call_output\", \"custom_tool_call\", \"custom_tool_call_output\". Explicitly skip payload.type \"reasoning\" (encrypted, hidden — must never be stored), and skip session_meta/turn_context/event_msg/world_state entirely (event_msg user_message/agent_message duplicate the response_item messages).\n\nMapping (seq = 0-based file line index over ALL lines):\n- kind: \"conversation_turn\"\n- occurred_at: line.timestamp if present, else payload timestamp-ish field if you find one, else a session base time: parse from the filename (rollout-YYYY-MM-DDThh-mm-ss-*.jsonl) if it matches, else file mtime. Same fallback value for every line is acceptable.\n- For payload.type \"message\": actor from payload.role → \"user\" → {type:\"human\"}, \"assistant\" → {type:\"agent\"}; content: { role: payload.role, blocks: payload.content mapped: {type:\"input_text\"|\"output_text\", text} → {type:\"text\", text}; unknown blocks kept verbatim }.\n- For function_call / custom_tool_call: actor {type:\"agent\"}; content { role: \"assistant\", blocks: [{type:\"tool_use\", name: payload.name, input: payload.arguments ?? payload.input, id: payload.call_id}] } (add fields only when present).\n- For function_call_output / custom_tool_call_output: actor {type:\"system\"}; content { role: \"tool_result\", blocks: [{type:\"tool_result\", tool_use_id: payload.call_id, content: payload.output}] }.\n- producer: { tool: \"cledger\", version as above, source: