st/test'`. I confirmed via Node's own current docs that directory args are no longer documented as supported; only glob patterns (`node --test \"dist/test/**/*.test.js\"`) or explicit files work, or zero-arg auto-discovery from cwd. This means the project's existing `\"test\": \"npm run build &amp;&amp; node --test dist/test/\"` script in `package.json` fails on this Node version regardless of test content — I verified this by running `npm test` as-is (fails with the error above) versus `node --test \"dist/test/**/*.test.js\"` from the built output (46/46 pass). Per instructions I did not modify `package.json` or any other non-test source file; flagging this here since it's the one thing standing between \"tests pass\" and \"`npm test` reports success\" in this sandbox.\n\nNo genuine bugs found in `canonical.ts`, `schema.ts`, `git.ts`, `store.ts`, or the two adapters — behavior matched the documented/intended design in every case I tested, including a couple of quirks worth being aware of (documented as current behavior, not treated as bugs): `readEvents` always includes pending (unborn-HEAD-queued) events regardless of the `reachableFrom` filter, since pending events have no anchor commit to filter against.</result>\n<usage><subagent_tokens>100708</subagent_tokens><tool_uses>44</tool_uses><duration_ms>604023</duration_ms></usage>\n</task-notification>","type":"text"}],"role":"user"},"context":{"cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evintunador/conversation-ledger","dirty_fingerprint":"e12e6fe04f3a78e3a5f3ff041be237d2a899e1d55f1148de6f18442622160697","repo":"conversation-ledger"},"conversation":{"id":"claude-code:700cd82f-2f79-4cd6-b727-0f81230e0837","seq":344},"id":"ev1-9b530d526847fb0fde7f6c52389956dc1312631fbc9fb243ccc9a4e8eac58b8e","kind":"conversation_turn","occurred_at":"2026-07-18T22:56:58.916Z","producer":{"session_id":"700cd82f-2f79-4cd6-b727-0f81230e0837","source":"claude-code","tool":"cledger","version":"0.1.0"},"raw":{"data":{"cwd":"/Users/evintunador/repos/evi